<br>
Combat is fairly straight forward.  You toggle Peace/War with the "c" key (rebindable), and doubleclick your target to engage in melee.  My personal experience with a Fighter has been that leveling is incredibly easy in the early stages.  There are plenty of mobs around the starting towns, which I should also mention are non-PvP areas.  Upon attaining your 10th level you are allowed to venture onto the larger continents and engage in PvP or what have you.  You are, however, allowed to stay on the pk-free continent until your 20th level should you chose.<br>
<br>
I can't comment on magic too much, other than a level 20 wizard seems incredibly powerful and they can easily powerlevel younger players.  So no worries about lagging behind your friends.<br>
<br>
Also I should mention that just about everything in the game can be bound to a key/key combination.  Very handy for keeping your spells/combat styles in check.<br>
<br>
Graphics Engine:  I honestly can't believe the flak people are throwing at Shadowbane's graphic engine.  When the server isn't lagging you or loading up new terrain, the engine runs quite smoothly.  Additionally the lighting is much better than what I was expecting.  Compared to DAoC the graphics are a step back (don't expect any DX8 pixel shaders), but their subdued nature suits the feel that Shadowbane is trying to achieve... a world torn by conflict.  There ain't no happy gnomes here folks.  In addition, while the player models aren't of extremely high polygon counts, they are smoothly animated, and textures are quite well done in most cases.  There are also a plethora of emotes that easily put DAoC's to shame.  ;)  Spell effects are also nice.<br>
<br>
Sound:  Music fits nicely with the game and sounds somewhat Diablo2ish at times.  Sound effects are also well done, and don't seem out of place.<br>
<br>
Character Creation and Customization:  Character creation is very straight forward.  You can pick skin tone, hair type, beard type and outfit.  You also start with 30 points to distribute between skills (str/con/etc), Runes (act like skills but have various effects), and different races (have various bonuses/faults).<br>
<br>
Skills:  There's an overwhelming number of paths one can chose.  I haven't leveled high enough to comment much on Professions and Disciplines, however I can say I do like the leveling system.  Whenver you level you get 5 skill points to allocate to your stats, as well as a training point that can be spent on your swordsmanship skill, magic skill, etc.<br>
<br>
Connectivity:  And now the pitfall.  Currently Shadowbane suffers from some fairly aweful lag problems (more so on the older server than the new one, Carnage).  Servers dropping, and errors happen occasionally, of course you'd be hardpressed to show me an MMORPG that didn't have connectivity issues before it's release.  Still, WP only has a month to work out these problems.<br>
<br>
I'm definitly looking forward to seeing how Shadowbane developes.  If WP can get past it's server issues, I won't have any problem ploppin down the cash when it hits retail. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#EBEFF1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mesmashyou>MeSmashYou</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#000000>(3/4/03 4:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Day 1 - Shadowbane - First Impressions</span><hr size=1> Stupid Next Games Board.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
